summary_to_eng: Incorrect response when token expired
Text_Summa: Incorrect response when token expired [Ulan Kozhomuratov|https://gitlab.com/isratmir] mentioned this issue in [a merge request of teacherly/teacherly|https://gitlab.com/teacherly/teacherly/merge_requests/1386]:[Ulan Kozhomuratov|https://gitlab.com/isratmir] mentioned this issue in [a commit of teacherly/teacherly|https://gitlab.com/teacherly/teacherly/commit/f0765e19846c8b7e7e654e40b0588d4787fcc76e]:it's gonna be difficult for the frontend to understand that token is incorrect. I suggest to treat invalid / expired tokens as expired. End user doesn't understand what JWT is and why its malformed / corrupted and thus should be redirected to login page. For simplicity's sake let's treat empty Authorization token as 400 and corrupted / malformed; expired as expired and return 401. Is it possible?

summary_to_eng: 10.2 - Whiteboard feature
Text_Summa: 10.2 - Whiteboard feature {quote}It's the action; when a teacher starts activity; it means that every student should have their own phase with the whiteboard toolbar enabled to draw; text etc… to complete teacher's tasks. Teacher can start activity and stop activity. After stopping activity on the student's side; the whiteboard toolbar should be blocked and all data(drawings; etc) should be stored inside the student's phase. Teacher should see students' phases and check them all. It could be attached to the student's camera view; or it could be a separate module or block with these phases.{quote}The most time efficient for the whiteboard feature is [https://zwibbler.com/|https://zwibbler.com/] it costs $3499 USD and it is only whiteboard library. It doesn't include screen broadcasting; chat and recording.

summary_to_eng: Remove css file duplicates
Text_Summa: Remove css file duplicates [~denis.petrov] need to pass this check; make it green.[ ~puzanov@gmail.com ]; Pagespeed simply checking above the fold content and % of styles it uses during rendering. Let's say we have 100kb of styles; above the fold content uses only 10kb. This tool suggests to write 10Kb of css inline and to load 90Kb later. There are a lot of stylesheets in magento in different modules; need to manually check every single one of them; find places which is used in above the fold content; and move them to inline. This is a lot of work. What I can do quick; it just load entire css later; but in this case; site will look in a following way while styles loading:Css duplicates have been removed. Merge service now works properly on the category/product/search page.seems working
